  "texts": [
    "First, the GPT series' pretraining relies on a large dataset with high-quality screening.",
    "GPT-2 used about 40 GB of pre-training data (Radford et al., 2019), while GPT-3 employed a dramatically larger volume of training data (about 45 TB) that underwent cleansing, evaluation, and quality screening (Brown et al., 2020).",
    "This kind of data processing is similar to what Dewey (2008) calls secondary or reflective experience, which is a continued and regulated reflective inquiry for experience.",
    "Second, the GPT series' pre-training involves unsupervised training (Radford et al., 2018 (Radford et al.,, 2019)), which does not require manual labelling of the collected corpus.",
    "The unsupervised training method employs the classic Language Modeling technique in natural language processing (Chowdhery et al., 2022): it inputs the first N words and requires the model to output the N + 1th word, then continuously corrects and optimizes to enable the model to learn natural language."
  ],
